dc_title_s: Map of the discoveries in Australia : copied from the latest M.S. Surveys in the Colonial Office
dc_description_s: Map of Southeastern Australia showing explorers routes for the period 1817-1830 and the nineteen counties in New South Wales. Relief shown by hachures.; Includes referenced table entitled: Reference to the tracks of the travellers and the number of miles explored by each.; At bottom right of sheet: 35.|46.8 x 61.5 centimeters|Scale approximately 1:2,900,000
dc_publisher_s: Pubd. by J. Arrowsmith,  33 East St. Red Lion Square (London)
